{
  "name": "Necklace of Prayer Beads",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"item-attunement\"><p><em>(Requires attunement by a Cleric, Druid, or Paladin)</em></p></div><p>This necklace can have magic beads, <strong>Prayer Beads</strong>, made from aquamarine, black pearl, topaz, ivory, bone, stone, amber, bloodstone, citrine, coral, jade, pearl, quartz, etc. If a <strong>Prayer Bead</strong> is removed from the necklace, that bead loses its magic until placed back on a <em>Necklace of Prayer Beads</em>.</p><p>Six types of magic beads exist. The GM decides the type of each bead on the necklace or determines it randomly. A necklace can have more than one bead of the same type. To use one, you must be wearing the necklace. Each bead contains a spell that you can cast from it as a <strong>Bonus Action</strong> (using your spell save DC if a save is necessary).</p><p><strong>Charges: </strong>The number of charges is based on what <strong>Prayer Beads</strong> are placed on this necklace. <em>(See your Prayer Bead item for Charge information).</em></p><p><strong>Recharge: </strong>Once a magic bead's spell is cast, that bead cannot be used again until the next dawn, unless stated otherwise.</p>",
